Week I: Infiltration&lt;/c&gt;<br>
<br>
&lt;b&gt;Day One<br>
Sunday, June 15, 2003&lt;/b&gt;<br>
<br>
Vicious pulled into the driveway of the small, run down house and killed the engine. He looked down at the information  he’d acquired by paying off a DMV worker about this guy he was trying to find. A Camarilla Brujah, apparently. Dean Halperin was his name, and he was apparently down here for a similar reason to Vicious’, except without the lofty “Kill or eat the Bishop of the city” goal. He was a very carefully placed spy who’d been here for months, and thus far had avoided detection. Vicious got out of the car and headed up to the front door, pausing for a moment to scan the door for traps before knocking. And waiting.<br>
<br>
“Who is it?” a gruff voice demanded from the other side. Vicious cocked his head to the side.<br>
<br>
“I got one word for you: Camarilla.” Vicious responded. The door was tossed open and Vicious was pulled inside by a massive arm that dragged him in and tossed him, apparently without effort, towards a nearby wall. Vicious easily absorbed the damage, but suddenly found himself face to face with a massive bear of a man. He was at least 6’9”, his arms almost the size of Vicous’ torso. A body that was made almost purely of muscle, and a face that made Vicious want to give up his current nickname, because he clearly wasn’t worthy of it when staring at this guy’s angry mug. A pair of angry green eyes stared into Vicious’ own eyes as he spoke.<br>
<br>
“Who the &lt;I&gt;fuck&lt;/I&gt; sent you?!” he demanded. Vicious took a moment, fighting off the urge to slip a carefully placed knife into Dean’s chest before responded.<br>
<br>
“Name’s Vicious, and if I &lt;I&gt;wasn’t&lt;/I&gt; Camarilla myself, don’t you think I’d’ve just blown the place up? Let’s be reasonable.” Vicious responded, hoping that the guy wasn’t &lt;I&gt;too&lt;/I&gt; paranoid. Not that Vicious blamed him.<br>
<br>
“Why the fuck should I believe you?!”<br>
<br>
Okay, so he was.<br>
<br>
“Well, I can give you the exact, current hierarchy of Santa Carla, a rough hierarchy of Portland until February, and here’s my Prince’s number.” Vicious said, reaching into his pocket and pulling out a card with Orlock’s phone number scrawled on it. Vicious had brought this for this exact reason. The Brujah took the card and his angry expressions softened slightly, but he still wasn’t convinced.<br>
<br>
“How do I know you’re not just fucking with me?” he asked in a low, hushed voice. Vicious rolled his eyes.<br>
<br>
“Look, honestly, I don’t really have the patience necessary to argue with you right now. You have no reason to trust me, I understand that. You can call the number and get in touch with the priice if that’ll convince you. If not, you can give that card back, I’ll take off, and you’ll never see me again. But as is, you’re kind of cutting into my ‘topple the Sabbat’ time right now, and I can probably convince the two little Torries in this city to help me instead. Now either stop trying to find reasons to kill me and back off, or I can show myself the door.”<br>
<br>
That did it. Dean finally took a step back and stared at Vicious with a slightly amused look on his face.<br>
<br>
“Well then, ‘Vicious’... What brings you here?”<br>
